ARCHITECTURAL: ToolGateway rewritten from scratch (Codex CNS-011 Yol C).

Old: 265-line subprocess-based dispatch via src.ops.manage (broken, dead)
New: 170-line callable-handler dispatch in ao_kernel/ (working, tested)

ao_kernel/tool_gateway.py:
- ToolGateway: authorize → dispatch → result (single dispatch path)
- ToolSpec: name, handler (callable), allowed, input_schema
- ToolCallPolicy: enabled, max_rounds, allow_unknown (fail-closed)
- ToolCallResult: OK | DENIED | ERROR

MCP integration:
- create_tool_gateway(): pre-configured with 4 governance tools
- call_tool → ToolGateway.authorize → handler → envelope
- Single dispatch path (no parallel dict dispatch)

Fail-closed:
- Unknown tool → DENIED
- Disallowed tool → DENIED
- Policy disabled → DENIED
- Max rounds exceeded → DENIED
- Handler error → ERROR (not silent allow)

21 new tests, 261 total passing.

